    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stacks of gold sheets, removed from the "cutches" grouping and cut into quarters, piled in a stack interleaved with goldbeater's skin and bound with parchment strips, to be beaten thinner in the second stage of producing gold leaf by hand before being moved to "molds (grouping for gold-shaping)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000044672/Barnes, Gilding (1962)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stapeltjes bladgoud, afkomstig uit de ‘cutches’, in vieren gesneden, op elkaar gestapeld met tussen de bladen goudslagersvlies en bij elkaar gebonden met perkamentstroken; worden platter geslagen in de tweede fase van de handmatige productie van bladgoud, voordat ze naar de ‘mallen voor bladgoud’ gaan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stapel Goldblätter, der von der "Quetsche (Metallbearbeitungswerkzeug)" entfernt und in Quadrate geschnitten wird, in einen Stapel geschichtet, der mit Goldschlägerhaut durchschossen und mit Pergamentstreifen gebunden ist, um in der zweiten Phase der manuellen Blattgoldherstellung dünner geschlagen zu werden, bevor er in die "Goldschlägerform" geschoben wird.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>從「打箔襯紙(塑金工具)」取出堆疊之金片，切割成小塊疊在一起，中間插入金箔匠用的牛腸膜將其隔開，並以羊皮紙條將其繫住。在手工打製金箔的第二階段中，將其打造得更為細薄，再移入「金箔模(塑金工具)」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
